fix(redraft): allow project status rewind from any later same-group status

Symptom
- Re-drafting a pre_report after it had already been "sent" left
  project.status at E3_prereport_sent while the document was reset to
  draft. The workflow header therefore kept showing "보고서 전달".
- Same potential bug existed for estimate (B3/B4) and contract (C3/C4)
  redraft paths.

Cause
- redraft / contract-redraft routes only rewound the project when its
  status equaled the review step (E2/B2/C2). Any later step in the same
  group skipped the project transition silently.

Fix
- ProjectService.transitionStatus accepts a new
  `allowRewindWithinGroup` option that, combined with
  `systemInitiated`, permits same-group rewinds even when the static
  transition table does not list them.
- redraft route now rewinds whenever project.status is in the same
  group and is not already at the target draft step. Logs a warning
  and skips when the project is in a different group.
- contract-redraft route applies the same rule for the C group.

Behavior change
- Re-drafting estimate / pre_report / contract from any later step in
  the same group now correctly rewinds the project to B1/E1/C1.
- Existing data with the mismatch must be repaired manually (DRY-RUN
  + UPDATE shared in chat). Triggers re-sync segments automatically.
